A former member of the Nigerian Senate, Shehu Sani, has said President Muhammadu Buhari would have protested if the government of ex-President Goodluck Jonathan piled up debts like he has done.In an ongoing Twitter Spaces session with Daily Trust, the Senator, who represented Kaduna Central in the 8th National Assembly, rated the government lowly. Shehu Sani



He said, “Never at a time as a country has Nigeria been in so much debt. We keep borrowing from everywhere.”He said whatever Buhari thought he had achieved would mean nothing if Nigerians were not secure.Sani also accused Buhari of keeping incompetent people in office, wondering why he cannot reshuffle his cabinet.